2011.assessment:
Minimal displacement. Bhutanese resettlement ~12,000 departed 2011;
approximately 55,000 remaining. Constitutional vacuum after CA expired
May 2011 but no displacement consequence. Stable security situation.

2012.assessment:
Minimal displacement. CA dissolved May 2012. Constitutional deadlock had
no displacement effects. Bhutanese resettlement continuing (~10,000/year);
approximately 45,000 remaining in Nepal camps. Stable.

1992.assessment:
No sanctions. Nepal receiving strong international development support
from bilateral donors (US, UK, Japan, India) and multilateral (World Bank,
ADB, UN agencies).
